main event: Three unidentified objects were observed in Xenia, Ohio on March 27, 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted between 5 to 10 minutes., The objects made a loud buzzing sound., Witnesses described the color of the objects as bright white with a bluish hue., The objects varied in size, with one described as football-like., The conclusion from the investigation stated there was insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: three unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: 17-year-old female with family members present during the sighting
